== 未來 ==
{{transh}}
A proposed extension from the line's Greenbelt terminus to [[Baltimore–Washington_International_Airport|Baltimore Washington International Airport]] has been studied.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/04/09/AR2006040901162.html Paley, Amit R. "Plan For Metro to BWI Gaining Momentum." ''Washington Post.'' April 10, 2006.]</ref> This expansion, which would also serve the [[Laurel,_Maryland|Laurel]] and [[Fort_Meade,_Maryland|Fort Meade]] areas of central Maryland,<ref name="meade">[http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/traffic/bal-md.ar.bases09jun09,1,1245355.story McGowan, Phillip. "Fort Meade Proposes Metro Extension."] ''[[The_Baltimore_Sun|The Baltimore Sun]]''. June 9, 2005.</ref> would link the Washington Metro system to the [[Light_RailLink|Baltimore Light Rail]] of the [[Maryland_Transit_Administration|Maryland Transit Administration]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mta.maryland.gov/services/bus/schedule/LRMAP209.pdf|title=Light Rail Map|publisher=Maryland Transit Administration|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101110160451/http://mta.maryland.gov/services/bus/schedule/LRMAP209.pdf|archive-date=November 10, 2010|url-status=dead|access-date=June 15, 2011}}</ref>
